Prostomium with well-defined anterior and posterior sections separated by a pair of deep transverse nuchal slits that meet mid-dorsally (
Fig. 6C
). Pigmented glandular bands above nuchal slits (
Fig. 6C
). Anterior part of prostomium whole, without any distinct lobes, and with a slightly raised lip. No eyespots present. Segments I and II obscured by branchial ridge. Segment I continued ventrally to form lower margin of the mouth no crenulations.

Lateral wings of anterior body between prostomium and segment V highly arched (
Fig. 6B
).

Segment I collar-like, laterally and ventrally encompassing head region. Branchiae emerging together on dorsal branchial ridge at level of segment II–III (
Fig. 7A
), arranged in two basally fused groups of four, three branchiae in front and one pair slightly behind (towards anterior). Inner- and anteriormost branchia of each group not joined by membrane. Branchiae circular in cross section, slightly ridged (
Fig. 7A
), dorsal groove, gently tapering to filiform tips. Branchiae roughly one third the length of longest buccal tentacle. Outer pair of branchiae longest (
Fig. 6B
).

Thoracic uncini in single line of around 43 (
Fig. 7D
). Abdominal uncini in a single line of 14 (
Fig. 7E
). Uncini of thoracic uncinigers with two teeth in one vertical row over rostral tooth, subrostral process and basal prow (
Fig. 7D
). Uncini of abdominal uncinigers with numerous teeth over rostral tooth, subrostral process and basal prow (
Fig. 7E
).

Pygidium with terminal crenulated anus, bounded by 4 small indistinct lobes. No anal cirri. (
Fig. 6a
).
